### **UNDRIP: Key Articles and Rights (Continued)**

UNDRIP’s **46 articles** are grouped thematically, balancing **individual rights** (e.g., life, liberty) with **collective rights** (e.g., self-determination, land stewardship). Below are the most impactful provisions, with real-world applications and ties to **Feedback Processor Theory (FPT)** and **Space Stewardship Compact (SSC)**.

---

#### **Core Rights by Category**

| **Category** | **Key Articles** | **Rights Affirmed** | **Real-World Example** |
|--------------|------------------|---------------------|------------------------|
| **Self-Determination** | **Art. 3–4** | Indigenous peoples have the right to **freely determine their political status** and pursue economic, social, and cultural development. Autonomy in internal affairs. | **Nunavut (Canada)**: Inuit-led territory since 1999, exercising self-governance under UNDRIP principles.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render> |
| **Lands, Territories, Resources** | **Art. 25–32** | Right to **own, use, develop, and control** traditional lands; **free, prior, and informed consent (FPIC)** for projects; redress for confiscated lands. | **Standing Rock (2016)**: Dakota Access Pipeline protests invoked UNDRIP’s FPIC; led to global solidarity and temporary rerouting.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render> |
| **Culture & Identity** | **Art. 11–13, 31** | Right to **practice and revitalize** cultural traditions, languages, and spiritual practices; control over **cultural heritage and intellectual property**. | **Māori Language Revival (NZ)**: UNDRIP supported te reo Māori co-official status and immersion schools.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render> |
| **Participation & Consent** | **Art. 18–19** | Right to **participate in decision-making** via chosen representatives; states must consult in **good faith** to obtain FPIC. | **Sami Parliament (Norway)**: Consultative body influencing Arctic policy.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render> |
| **Treaty Rights** | **Art. 37** | Right to **honor and enforce treaties** with states. | **U.S. Supreme Court (2020)**: McGirt v. Oklahoma affirmed Muscogee (Creek) Nation treaty lands using UNDRIP-aligned logic.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
<argument name="citation_id">0</argument>
</grok:render> |

> **Article 46**: No provision allows secession or actions that impair territorial integrity—addressing state fears.<grok:render type="render_inline_citation">
